ea-sensitivity or edge-avoidance were found, harmful consequences of forest shredding following forest logging may still occur for boreal species such as the Three-toed Woodpecker. However, residual forests strips are essential to maintain this species within managed areas. its population density within such residual forests being comparable to the one obtained in continuous forests. (C) 2002 Elsevier Science B.V. All rights reserved.
